cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with deep learning approaches to face recognition and facial landmark detection, which are both subfields of computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the use of synthetic data to reduce the negative effects of dataset biases, which is a topic related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves the use of 3D models to generate synthetic face images, which is a topic related to computer graphics (GR), making it a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the evaluation of performance on benchmarks, which is a topic related to multimedia (MM), making it a possible sub-category as well.
